rdf:Description.ns3:description:
Monk is the core ontology linked with Monkology.
It is designed to help represent the following elements in ontologies.
* SparqlVirtualFields * Private/Public data * Revision and migration information * Journalized data * Fuzzy data (with some uncertainty) * Inherited objects * Copy-on-write * Units standards
Monkology and Monk Ontotlogy are currently under active development.
